\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 The Real Stakes: Avoiding the Thucydides Trap\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Historically, when a rising power threatens to displace a ruling one, war becomes likely. This is the 
\f0\b Thucydides Trap
\f1\b0 , and many believe we are entering one now\'97only this time, the stakes are even higher. Instead of traditional war, we risk a technological domination that could cement inequalities, break democratic systems, and endanger human alignment with superintelligence.\
PRSM sidesteps this trap by distributing power from the outset. It provides a framework where national, institutional, and individual actors can 
\f0\b benefit by cooperating
\f1\b0  rather than racing.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
